## Create a catalog item

```shell
curl "https://api.invoiced.com/catalog_items" \
  -u {API_KEY}: \
  -d id="delivery" \
  -d name="Delivery" \
  -d type="service" \
  -d unit_cost=100
```

```ruby
invoiced.CatalogItem.create(
  :id => "delivery",
  :name => "Delivery",
  :type => "service",
  :unit_cost => 100
)
```

```php
<?php

$invoiced->CatalogItem->create([
  'id' => "delivery",
  'name' => "Delivery",
  'type' => "service",
  'unit_cost' => 100
]);
```

```python
client.CatalogItem.create(
  id="delivery",
  name="Delivery",
  type="service",
  unit_cost=100
)
```

```java
CatalogItem catalogItem = invoiced.newCatalogItem();
catalogItem.id = "delivery";
catalogItem.name = "Delivery";
catalogItem.type = "service";
catalogItem.unitCost = 100;
catalogItem.create();
```

